CARACAS -- Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez expressed his concern Saturday over a lawsuit filed by a group of small U.S. oil producers about alleged unfair practices in Venezuelan and Mexican oil prices. 

 In his letter to U.S. President Bill Clinton, published by the Presidency of the Republic, Chavez called on Clinton's attention to the matter, considered to be "of utmost importance" for Venezuela. (Venezuela-US-Oil) 

