 BAGHDAD -- Iraq and Tunisia started trade talks here on Saturday and the two countries pledged to expand commercial exchanges, the Iraqi News Agency (INA) reported. 

 The talks were co-chaired by Iraqi Trade Minister Mohammed Mehdi Saleh and his Tunisian counterpart Mondher Zenaidi, said INA. 

 Saleh reiterated in the talks Iraq's readiness to expand commercial exchanges with Arab countries. (Iraq-Tunisia-Trade Talks) 

