 DHAKA -- Bangladesh's export of raw jute declined by 26 percent in the just-concluded 1998-99 fiscal year as compared with that in the previous year, The Financial Express reported Saturday. 

 The country earned 3.24 billion taka (2.02 million U.S. dollars) by exporting 1.76 million bales (one bale equivalent to 180 kilograms) in the last fiscal year, against 4.3 billion taka (86.9 million dollars) from the export of 2.4 million bales of raw jute in the previous fiscal year, the report said, quoting sources of the Bangladesh Jute Association. (Bangladesh-Jute Export) 

